:INFO
The Most Common Bokashi Problems and How to Fix Them
Most bokashi problems come down to one of three things: \
not enough bran, too much air in the bucket, or the wrong moisture level in the scraps. \
This page covers the issues people encounter most often and what they actually mean. \
None of them require starting over from scratch unless mold has turned green or black.

